<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Development-of-unique-maize-source-germplasm-for-African-ecosystems" title="Development of unique maize source germplasm for African ecosystems" alt="document">Development of unique maize source germplasm for African ecosystems</a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>Maize is the major food security and economic crop in east and southern Africa, and occupies 62% to 98% of the land allocated to cereal grains in the region. However, maize grain production is still not adequate to sustain a rapidly growing population; maize production rate does not match population growth in the sub-continent.</p>
