						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Agricultural-Biotechnology-Issues-for-Biosafety-Governance-in-Asian-Countries" title="Agricultural Biotechnology: Issues for Biosafety Governance in Asian Countries" alt="link">Agricultural Biotechnology: Issues for Biosafety Governance in Asian Countries</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>P.G. Sampath, UNU-Intech Discussion paper 13, 2004</i>. The potential risks imposed by GM crops on the environment can be grouped into four main categories - the creation of invasive weeds or insect species, loss of agricultural diversity due to monocultures and contamination of the gene pools of wild species. This paper analyses the gravity of these risks and the issues of governance they raise. It derives conclusions for policy making in the realm of environmental governance (in terms of biosafety) so that the benefits of agricultural biotechnology eventually do exceed the costs.</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Agricultural-Biotechnology-Issues-for-Biosafety-Governance-in-Asian-Countries">Read more...</a>
