						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Perspectives-on-agricultural-transformation-A-view-from-Africa-Sustainable-agriculture-in-Eastern-and-Central-Africa" title="Perspectives on agricultural transformation: A view from Africa - Sustainable agriculture in Eastern and Central Africa" alt="link">Perspectives on agricultural transformation: A view from Africa - Sustainable agriculture in Eastern and Central Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>
By T.S. Jayne; I. Minde; G. Argwings-Kodhek, Association for Strengthening Agricultural Research in Eastern and Central Africa, 2004 This book provides a predominantly African perspective on the nature of the agricultural development crisis, and the challenges posed by globalisation, biotechnology, policy reform, and widespread poverty. Most of the twenty-one contributors to this volume are African agriculturalists and development economists who live and work on the continent. </p>
							<p><span class="date">2/06/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Perspectives-on-agricultural-transformation-A-view-from-Africa-Sustainable-agriculture-in-Eastern-and-Central-Africa">Read more...</a>
